          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "LU-4800 llite: handle lustre fs registration properly for newer kernels",
        "message": "LU-4800 llite: handle lustre fs registration properly for newer kernels\n\nWith newer kernels running the mount command no longers properly loads\nthe kernel modules needed so a client mount fails. This patch addresses\nthis by loading the module lustre in the obdclass module when the routine\nlustre_fill_super is executed. We also avoid the module cycular dependency\nbetween these two modules by using symbol_get to retrieve the functions\nfrom llite to be executed in the obdclass context.\n\nChange-Id: I4d091bb8ba94be07a01146031b1c097565ba113e\nSigned-off-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@gmail.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
